      <bioghist encodinganalog="545">
         <head>Biographical History</head>
         
      <p>Herbert Beckhard (1926-2003) was an American architect. With Frank Richlan, he was a
            founding member of the achitectural firm Herbert Beckhard Frank Richlan and Associates
            in 1982. Previously, Beckhard was associate architect, and later partner, in the firm
            Marcel Breuer and Associates (later MBA Architects and Planners). </p></bioghist>
      
      <scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
         <head>Scope and Contents of the Collection</head>
         <p>The <emph render="bold">Herbert Beckhard Papers</emph> consists of office
            records, project files, photographs, architectural drawings,  architectural models and
            project presentation materials (mounted drawings, photos and renderings). Most of the
            material relates to work done by the firm Herbert Beckhard Frank Richlan and Associates
            (1982-2003). There is a small amount of material related to the firm Marcel Breuer and
            Associates (later MBA Architects and Planners).</p>
      </scopecontent>
      
      <arrangement encodinganalog="351$a">
